The paper deals with the problem of summarizing a stream of votes and determining the winner using computational social choice theory. This involves designing data structures and algorithms to efficiently process and analyze large amounts of data. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The paper also involves game theory (cs.GT), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), machine learning (cs.LG), and social networks (cs.SI) as it deals with voting rules and determining winners in social settings.
